♪ Got a big black hole

01:44.016 --> 01:47.585
♪ Got a big black hole

01:47.629 --> 01:51.415
♪ I've got a big black hole

01:51.459 --> 01:55.550
♪ I've got a big black,
big black hole ♪

01:55.593 --> 01:59.641
♪ Got a big black hole
inside of me ♪

01:59.684 --> 02:01.338
♪ Got a

02:03.906 --> 02:05.429
♪ Dance to the sound
of the merry-go-round ♪

02:05.473 --> 02:07.127
♪ But you know that
you gotta get off ♪

02:07.170 --> 02:08.519
♪ You're a slave to the wage,
and you're underpaid ♪

02:08.563 --> 02:10.521
♪ But everybody needs a job

02:10.565 --> 02:12.393
♪ When will you learn
that there's money to burn ♪

02:12.436 --> 02:14.612
♪ But there's nothing
to give to you? ♪

02:14.656 --> 02:16.440
♪ Don't be afraid
to walk your own way ♪

02:16.484 --> 02:18.094
♪ You gotta do
what you gotta do ♪

02:18.138 --> 02:20.096
♪ So, why you running away?

02:20.140 --> 02:22.664
♪ Why you running away?

02:22.707 --> 02:25.406
♪ Everybody jump
if you wanna jump ♪

02:25.449 --> 02:27.190
♪ Do you wanna jump?

02:27.234 --> 02:29.845
♪ Everybody jump
if you wanna jump ♪

02:29.888 --> 02:31.107
♪ Do you wanna jump?

02:31.151 --> 02:34.545
♪ Jump

02:34.589 --> 02:36.765
Hey.

02:38.680 --> 02:42.553
How much are we gonna get
for this Eddie Pham job?

02:42.597 --> 02:45.469
It's hard to tell until
Craig scouts the place.

02:45.513 --> 02:48.646
It depends if they do
the manufacturing on-site.

02:48.690 --> 02:52.824
I need like 50K
for my cut.

02:52.868 --> 02:55.000
For your skate park?

02:55.044 --> 02:58.308
Yeah.
Cement ain't cheap.

02:58.352 --> 03:00.658
I don't want to build
a bowl.

03:00.702 --> 03:03.313
Are you gonna
charge people?

03:05.315 --> 03:06.621
To skate?

03:06.664 --> 03:08.188
How about if you make it
a nonprofit?

03:08.231 --> 03:09.493
That way,
nothing has to change

03:09.537 --> 03:11.800
and we can start
pushing money through it.

03:11.843 --> 03:15.934
Nobody's paying,
so it already is a nonprofit.

03:15.978 --> 03:18.328
So, is that a yes?

03:22.854 --> 03:24.552
Maybe.

03:30.732 --> 03:32.255
Ahh!

03:32.299 --> 03:36.477
[ Both breathing heavily ]

03:50.099 --> 03:53.102
Did you even
lock the door?

03:53.145 --> 03:55.322
Nobody ever
comes in here.

03:57.802 --> 03:59.543
Love the ambiance.

03:59.587 --> 04:02.416
[ Sniffs ]
It's very romantic.

04:04.548 --> 04:06.507
How long does it take you
to sell all this booze?

04:06.550 --> 04:07.725
[ Lighter clicks ]

04:07.769 --> 04:09.510
I don't know.
A couple months.

04:09.553 --> 04:10.902
[ Exhales sharply ]

04:10.946 --> 04:12.861
I guess the place
is pretty packed.

04:12.904 --> 04:14.732
People like to drink.

04:14.776 --> 04:16.778
I don't think
it's the booze.

04:19.084 --> 04:20.695
I think it's you.

04:20.738 --> 04:23.828
See, you're kind of
like the man around here --

04:23.872 --> 04:26.701
the beach, in town.

04:29.007 --> 04:30.313
Everyone knows you.

04:30.357 --> 04:33.664
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

04:33.708 --> 04:36.450
Who's J?

04:38.843 --> 04:41.193
[ Exhales sharply ]
My nephew.

04:41.237 --> 04:42.760
You know, it feels like

04:42.804 --> 04:46.895
I'm the only one who doesn't
know anything about you.

04:46.938 --> 04:50.290
Just come when you call,
then I leave.

04:50.333 --> 04:54.903
The sex is...great,

04:54.946 --> 04:57.471
but I can get that
in San Diego.

05:00.169 --> 05:04.260
So, what do you want?

05:04.304 --> 05:07.263
More than this.

05:07.307 --> 05:11.702
Come on.
I'm not asking for much.

05:15.010 --> 05:18.100
I just want to get
to know you better.

05:18.143 --> 05:20.015
And go someplace nice.

05:21.930 --> 05:24.976
Yeah, well, I'll come down
to San Diego or something.

05:25.020 --> 05:32.941
♪♪

05:32.984 --> 05:34.899
Thank you.

05:37.511 --> 05:40.514
Oh, shit.
Gotta go.

05:43.212 --> 05:45.475
[ Door opens ]

05:45.519 --> 05:47.782
[ Door closes ]

05:47.825 --> 05:51.481
♪♪

05:51.525 --> 05:54.702
[ Seagull crying ]

06:03.928 --> 06:05.408
Morning.

06:05.452 --> 06:07.541
Morning.

06:13.547 --> 06:16.114
[ Pounding on door ]

06:17.551 --> 06:20.467
You gonna get that?

06:20.510 --> 06:22.033
-No.
-[ Chuckles ]

06:22.077 --> 06:24.035
Good.

06:24.079 --> 06:26.995
[ Pounding continues ]

06:27.038 --> 06:28.866
Oh, my God.

06:31.303 --> 06:33.131
[ Knock on door ]

06:35.482 --> 06:37.788
What are you doing here,
man?

06:37.832 --> 06:40.661
Holding boundaries.
I like that.

06:40.704 --> 06:41.879
Yeah.

06:41.923 --> 06:43.446
[ Laughs ]

06:43.490 --> 06:45.317
Nah, man, I was, uh,
headed to the shop.

06:45.361 --> 06:47.363
Thought I'd come by to check
on you, see how you're doing.

06:47.407 --> 06:49.626
Mm?
Nah, I'm doing good.

06:49.670 --> 06:51.541
-Okay?
-Yeah.

06:51.585 --> 06:53.674
Hey, uh, I was thinking about
what you said,

06:53.717 --> 06:55.806
about wanting to move.
-Mm-hmm?

06:55.850 --> 06:58.374
I think
it's a good idea.

06:58.418 --> 07:01.508
Old places keep you
in old habits.

07:01.551 --> 07:03.901
Hey, Vince.

07:03.945 --> 07:05.903
Brittany.

07:05.947 --> 07:08.166
Thanks, hon.

07:08.210 --> 07:09.733
You want one?

07:09.777 --> 07:11.735
No.

07:11.779 --> 07:14.303
I'm gonna
take a shower.

07:14.346 --> 07:16.044
What? Now?

07:16.087 --> 07:17.828
Yeah. Now.

07:21.745 --> 07:24.052
So, what's up, man?

07:26.141 --> 07:29.927
Buddy of mine
is renting out his condo.

07:29.971 --> 07:32.060
Thought you might
wanna check it out.

07:32.103 --> 07:33.278
Where?

07:33.322 --> 07:35.672
Over by
the golf course.

07:35.716 --> 07:37.674
Yeah, that's kinda far
from the beach.

07:37.718 --> 07:40.547
And all the bullshit
that come with it.

07:40.590 --> 07:42.853
Yeah, I dunno, man.

07:42.897 --> 07:46.466
When you get sober,
shit has to change.

07:46.509 --> 07:48.946
You know that.

07:48.990 --> 07:51.819
You said this used to be
your brother's place, right?

07:51.862 --> 07:53.951
Yeah.

07:53.995 --> 07:56.214
Lotta history.

07:56.258 --> 07:58.608
Hard to let go.

07:58.652 --> 08:01.481
Sometimes,
that's what it takes.

08:03.091 --> 08:06.398
I'm having a poker game later.
You should come on by.

08:06.442 --> 08:08.792
Frank will be there, and he can
tell you all about the place

08:08.836 --> 08:10.794
while I take your money.

08:10.838 --> 08:13.623
Yeah, well,
we'll see about that.

08:14.885 --> 08:17.801
-Alright, I'm out, man.
-Yeah, bro, man.

08:21.979 --> 08:23.677
So?

08:23.720 --> 08:25.156
What am I looking at?

08:25.200 --> 08:26.636
Mu future, I think.

08:26.680 --> 08:28.333
I want to buy it.

08:28.377 --> 08:30.161
What do you think?

08:30.205 --> 08:31.554
Can you afford it?

08:31.598 --> 08:32.860
I can get a loan.

08:32.903 --> 08:34.775
One of the partners thinks
I have a crush on him.

08:34.818 --> 08:37.560
He co-signed my car.
He can make this happen.

08:37.604 --> 08:39.823
What does your husband think
about that?

08:39.867 --> 08:42.739
Do you really care
what my husband thinks?

08:46.264 --> 08:47.831
Some minor renovations,

08:47.875 --> 08:50.007
the place should
fill up pretty fast.

08:50.051 --> 08:51.966
I'm not planning
to rent it out.

08:52.009 --> 08:53.750
A developer's buying up
most of the block,

08:53.794 --> 08:55.447
gonna build
an outdoor mall.

08:55.491 --> 08:57.841
I figure I hold on to this,
and it's only a matter of time

08:57.885 --> 09:00.235
before someone
gives me an offer.

09:00.278 --> 09:02.367
Where'd you find out
a mall's being built?

09:02.411 --> 09:05.806
It's not public, but one of
our clients is an investor.

09:05.849 --> 09:08.069
You looked through
a client's file?

09:08.112 --> 09:11.072
I'm a secretary, J.
I get bored.

09:11.115 --> 09:14.945
There's a better option,
if you're interested.

09:14.989 --> 09:16.773
I am.

09:16.817 --> 09:18.819
Tear it down,
build a parking lot.

09:18.862 --> 09:20.211
That way,
when the mall's built,

09:20.255 --> 09:22.997
you can make your money back
within a year.

09:23.040 --> 09:25.129
Then if they decide
to expand,

09:25.173 --> 09:27.828
they're gonna be forced
to buy you out.

09:27.871 --> 09:31.919
Okay. Yeah.
That's a much better idea.

09:33.616 --> 09:35.879
I have to get to work.

09:35.923 --> 09:37.577
Okay.

09:37.620 --> 09:41.711
Hey, uh, can I take you out to
dinner tonight, as a thank-you?

09:41.755 --> 09:44.627
You don't have to
do that.

09:44.671 --> 09:46.716
You just gave me
a million-dollar idea.

09:46.760 --> 09:49.066
I kinda do.

09:49.110 --> 09:50.459
Okay, sure.

09:50.502 --> 09:52.679
Great.
I'll text you.

09:57.597 --> 10:00.077
[ Computer powers on ]
-I thought Gia got all of those.

10:00.121 --> 10:02.906
Nah. That would have
been a waste.

10:02.950 --> 10:06.431
Brains need shit like this
for school and stuff.

10:06.475 --> 10:08.912
Here, come on.

10:08.956 --> 10:11.741
[ Chair slides
across floor ]

10:11.785 --> 10:14.570
Does it have
any programs?

10:14.614 --> 10:16.485
Yeah. Here.

10:16.528 --> 10:18.792
Check it out.

10:18.835 --> 10:20.010
[ Mouse clicks ]

10:20.054 --> 10:21.446
That's pretty cool,
right?

10:21.490 --> 10:23.144
Mari, come on.

10:23.187 --> 10:25.668
My guy is waiting
for the cars.

10:25.712 --> 10:28.758
He's ready to pay out.

10:28.802 --> 10:30.847
Mari!
[ Line clicks, dial tone ]

10:30.891 --> 10:32.980
[ Clicks tongue ]
Shit.

10:33.850 --> 10:35.591
[ Telephone beeps ]

10:35.635 --> 10:37.811
[ Sets telephone down ]

10:43.773 --> 10:46.123
[ Sighs ]

10:46.167 --> 10:47.429
Baz?

10:51.259 --> 10:54.566
♪♪

10:54.610 --> 10:56.960
-Mm.
-You wanna try a game?

10:57.004 --> 10:59.223
They're in this folder
right there.

10:59.267 --> 11:00.660
[ Chuckles ]

11:00.703 --> 11:01.791
Hey, Smurf.

11:01.835 --> 11:05.055
I thought we sold those
to Gia.

11:05.099 --> 11:06.404
Uh...

11:06.448 --> 11:08.450
Baz saved one.
For me.

11:08.493 --> 11:09.799
It wasn't up to him.

11:09.843 --> 11:11.496
It was his job.

11:11.540 --> 11:15.762
♪♪

11:15.805 --> 11:18.503
Where's your brother?

11:18.547 --> 11:20.462
Church.

11:20.505 --> 11:22.420
Again?

11:22.464 --> 11:24.858
He likes it.

11:27.730 --> 11:29.819
Lunch is ready.

11:31.342 --> 11:33.344
Hey, Smurf...

11:35.259 --> 11:36.696
[ Sighs ]

11:36.739 --> 11:42.179
♪♪

11:42.223 --> 11:44.355
Smurf, I'll pay you back,
okay?

11:44.399 --> 11:45.574
With what?

11:45.617 --> 11:47.184
I'll find something.

11:47.228 --> 11:51.362
Well, I hope so, because
my job just went to shit.

11:52.755 --> 11:55.279
Got bills to pay.

11:55.323 --> 11:57.281
What happened?

11:57.325 --> 11:58.848
[ Sighs ]

11:58.892 --> 12:01.372
Mari and Lorenzo
got cold feet.

12:01.416 --> 12:03.853
You don't need
Mari or Lorenzo.

12:03.897 --> 12:06.160
We can do it.
-Just the two of us?

12:06.203 --> 12:08.815
No, Julia and Andrew, too.
We can figure it out.

12:08.858 --> 12:13.123
♪♪

12:13.167 --> 12:14.777
[ Refrigerator door closes ]

12:16.910 --> 12:19.303
[ Sighs ]

12:19.347 --> 12:26.876
♪♪

12:26.920 --> 12:28.486
Thank you.

12:28.530 --> 12:30.271
Yeah.

12:32.055 --> 12:34.536
You should eat up.

12:34.579 --> 12:38.148
♪♪

12:43.588 --> 12:46.374
[ Indistinct talking,
telephones ringing ]

12:48.985 --> 12:52.206
Hey.
What's this?

12:52.249 --> 12:54.774
A request for a warrant
in the Catherine Belen case,

12:54.817 --> 12:56.645
for Andrew Cody's house.

12:56.688 --> 12:57.951
Oh, yeah?
On what cause?

12:57.994 --> 12:59.604
Lena Blackwell told me
that the night

12:59.648 --> 13:01.128
her mother
went missing,

13:01.171 --> 13:03.739
she fell asleep and woke up
in her Uncle Pope's truck.

13:03.783 --> 13:05.393
And this "Uncle Pope"
is Andrew Cody?

13:05.436 --> 13:07.264
Yeah. I think
he was the last person

13:07.308 --> 13:09.353
to see Catherine Belen
alive.

13:09.397 --> 13:11.094
-And Lena told you this?
-Yes.

13:11.138 --> 13:12.835
Was it the day you picked her up
from school

13:12.879 --> 13:15.229
or the one you took her
for ice cream?

13:16.621 --> 13:18.972
-I asked a couple questions.
-Damn it, Louise.

13:19.015 --> 13:21.409
You spoke to a child
without her parents' consent.

13:21.452 --> 13:23.672
Her father is dead, and somebody
buried her mother in the desert.

13:23.715 --> 13:25.761
Well, her adoptive parents,
then. And they're pissed.

13:25.805 --> 13:28.111
-Okay, so I'll send them
a fruit basket.
-Shut up!

13:28.155 --> 13:30.461
I had dinner with Jim Sandoval
last night,

13:30.505 --> 13:32.289
and he told me
all about what you did.

13:32.333 --> 13:35.292
I don't need any of
that bullshit here.

13:35.336 --> 13:44.301
♪♪

13:44.345 --> 13:53.136
♪♪

13:53.180 --> 13:55.399
How was church, baby?

13:59.142 --> 14:00.970
You didn't say
I couldn't go.

14:01.014 --> 14:03.407
I told you it was
a waste of your time.

14:03.451 --> 14:05.845
But you keep going.

14:05.888 --> 14:08.760
Is it a girl?

14:08.804 --> 14:11.502
Someone you like there?

14:11.546 --> 14:13.896
No.

14:17.030 --> 14:19.641
What kind of girls
doyou like?

14:19.684 --> 14:21.338
I don't know.

14:21.382 --> 14:23.166
Curvy?

14:23.210 --> 14:25.212
Tall?

14:26.474 --> 14:28.955
You like beachy girls?
-[ Sighs ]

14:28.998 --> 14:32.872
Don't be embarrassed.
It's normal.

14:32.915 --> 14:37.224
Although, that church of yours
would tell you differently.

14:40.140 --> 14:43.012
Don't go back there,
okay?

14:43.056 --> 14:46.059
They'll just make you
hate yourself.

14:47.408 --> 14:51.325
And I love you
too much for that.

14:51.368 --> 15:00.943
♪♪

15:00.987 --> 15:11.084
♪♪

15:13.042 --> 15:14.957
Man, I would have killed
for a place like this

15:15.001 --> 15:17.177
when we were kids.

15:24.010 --> 15:26.055
J: This is sick.

15:27.448 --> 15:28.840
Yeah!

15:28.884 --> 15:30.494
Deran:
Looks great, Pope.

15:30.538 --> 15:33.410
Nice.
Looks like the groms dig it.

15:33.454 --> 15:34.977
You did this
all by yourself?

15:35.021 --> 15:36.674
Me and Auge.

15:36.718 --> 15:38.241
-Who?
-Guy I pay.

15:38.285 --> 15:40.983
We should get him
on the payroll.

15:41.027 --> 15:43.594
I pay him in cash.

15:43.638 --> 15:45.118
Hey.

15:45.161 --> 15:47.468
Time's the meeting?

15:48.730 --> 15:50.471
Later.

15:50.514 --> 15:53.474
You gonna go
dressed like that?

15:53.517 --> 15:55.128
No.

15:55.171 --> 15:58.000
And I got a Maybach.

15:58.044 --> 16:00.481
Okay.
Why'd you get the Maybach?

16:00.524 --> 16:02.962
Because kiss-ass jewelry
designers like Eddie Pham

16:03.005 --> 16:04.876
give a shit
what you ride up in.

16:04.920 --> 16:06.966
Can't just be pulling up
in a Hyundai.

16:07.009 --> 16:10.230
-Where did you get it?
-Stole it. What do you think?

16:11.796 --> 16:13.973
Loaned it from Brad.

16:14.016 --> 16:15.191
Well,
what'd you tell Brad?

16:15.235 --> 16:16.801
Nothing, man, alright?

16:16.845 --> 16:18.978
Jesus. I'm out.

16:25.723 --> 16:28.161
[ Motorcycle engine starts ]

16:32.078 --> 16:33.296
Whoa!

16:33.340 --> 16:34.602
-Oof.
-Oof.

16:34.645 --> 16:36.256
You got insurance
on this place?

16:36.299 --> 16:38.171
Pope:
I don't need insurance.

16:38.214 --> 16:40.042
I think
he would say otherwise.

16:40.086 --> 16:42.175
I didn't tell that guy
to come here.

16:42.218 --> 16:44.829
Yeah, but you didn't
ask him to leave.

16:44.873 --> 16:47.441
That makes you responsible
if anything were to happen.

16:47.484 --> 16:49.617
All of our assets are tied
together at this point.

16:49.660 --> 16:52.228
Anything happens to you,
it happens to us.

16:52.272 --> 16:56.450
Hmm.
Starting to sound like him.

16:58.843 --> 17:00.889
Just saying.

17:00.932 --> 17:07.156
♪♪

17:07.200 --> 17:09.289
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh

17:09.332 --> 17:11.987
♪ Follow the leader

17:12.031 --> 17:14.076
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh

17:14.120 --> 17:15.643
♪ You better follow the leader

17:15.686 --> 17:18.080
♪ If you wanna ride this wave

17:18.124 --> 17:21.997
♪ If you wanna walk this way

17:22.041 --> 17:24.347
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh

17:24.391 --> 17:26.088
♪ Follow the leader

17:26.132 --> 17:29.004
Welcome, Mr. Smith.
Prosecco?

17:29.048 --> 17:30.397
Uh, do you have
anything virgin?

17:30.440 --> 17:32.660
Pellegrino,
in the tall glass.

17:32.703 --> 17:34.053
Thank you.

17:34.096 --> 17:35.619
♪ I've written it off

17:35.663 --> 17:38.057
♪ Real...the flow is diamond,
I still dip it in gold ♪

17:38.100 --> 17:40.624
♪ So you better watch your
whylin', never listen at all ♪

17:40.668 --> 17:42.452
♪ Nah, it's pissin' me off

17:42.496 --> 17:44.889
♪ I kick those and cock that,
reload and drop that ♪

17:44.933 --> 17:48.502
♪ For the fo', we get mo',
grab the po', we kick back ♪

17:48.545 --> 17:50.547
♪ I'm still trippin' on you

17:50.591 --> 17:53.115
♪ Ask me 'bout my plans,
I'ma tell you what I do ♪

17:53.159 --> 17:56.162
♪ I'm a girl that find a man, so
I'm not waitin' on your move ♪

17:56.205 --> 17:59.382
♪ Maybe we can move slow, baby

17:59.426 --> 18:01.776
♪ And I'm still trippin'
on you ♪

18:01.819 --> 18:04.257
♪ Ask me 'bout my plans,
I'ma tell you what I do ♪

18:04.300 --> 18:08.522
♪ I'm a girl that find a man, so
I'm not waitin' on your move ♪

18:08.565 --> 18:11.046
♪ Maybe we can move slow, baby

18:11.090 --> 18:13.266
I call that one
"The Flow."

18:14.136 --> 18:17.052
The Flow?
Right on.

18:17.096 --> 18:19.228
Eddie Pham.

18:20.142 --> 18:22.144
Caleb Smith.

18:22.188 --> 18:24.103
♪ Oh

18:24.146 --> 18:27.106
So, what do you want,
Caleb Smith?

18:27.149 --> 18:29.717
Looking for some rings.

18:29.760 --> 18:32.459
Palladium.

18:33.895 --> 18:36.767
You roll with a palladium ring,
people will say,

18:36.811 --> 18:38.465
"Is that platinum?"

18:38.508 --> 18:40.771
They'll Google that shit
and find out.

18:40.815 --> 18:45.950
That, uh, palladium's at,
uh, $25.65 an ounce today.

18:45.994 --> 18:48.127
Platinum's at $12.25.

18:48.170 --> 18:49.650
Sorry about him.

18:49.693 --> 18:52.566
Anyway, they'll find out
that the piece --

18:52.609 --> 18:56.135
and the man wearing it -- is
worth twice what they thought.

18:56.178 --> 18:59.834
Let's make this happen, alright?
I'm all cash, so let's do it.

18:59.877 --> 19:03.359
Next step is
Arthur here.

19:03.403 --> 19:05.883
He makes a mold
of your hand.

19:05.927 --> 19:08.712
Don't worry. That face of his
ain't contagious.

19:08.756 --> 19:11.019
-Nah, man, he's alright.
-Eh, you don't have to
be polite.

19:11.062 --> 19:15.110
I mean, Frankenstein wears a
mask of my brother on Halloween.

19:15.154 --> 19:17.460
♪♪

19:17.504 --> 19:19.680
Then we use
a 3-D printer

19:19.723 --> 19:22.204
to make the exact contours
of the piece.

19:22.248 --> 19:25.338
You and me sit down
and talk design.

19:25.381 --> 19:28.210
And that all happens
in here?

19:29.255 --> 19:32.258
All production
is done on-site.

19:32.301 --> 19:33.650
Every last carat.

19:33.694 --> 19:36.697
♪ Then nothin'
will come your way ♪

19:38.873 --> 19:41.180
It's for you.

19:41.223 --> 19:42.833
This my salary?

19:42.877 --> 19:44.748
Mm-hmm.

19:44.792 --> 19:48.187
It's 20 grand.
Where's the rest of it?

19:48.230 --> 19:51.973
In our bank account.
Safe.

19:53.844 --> 19:56.369
I wanted to talk to you
about that.

19:56.412 --> 19:58.719
I've been doing
some research.

19:58.762 --> 20:00.982
I think we should look into
setting up a trust,

20:01.025 --> 20:03.245
give us some
tax protection.

20:03.289 --> 20:05.856
Or we could keep it
in the storage unit.

20:05.900 --> 20:09.033
IRS doesn't know about it.
We all have access to it.

20:09.077 --> 20:10.861
Yeah, but sitting on money
is wasting money

20:10.905 --> 20:12.863
when it should be
working for us.

20:12.907 --> 20:14.213
What?
Like stocks?

20:14.256 --> 20:16.519
Stocks, bonds,
hedge funds.

20:16.563 --> 20:19.174
The trust
can do everything.

20:19.218 --> 20:21.350
So, we're back
on allowance?

20:21.394 --> 20:23.265
Yeah, but only
to build capitol.

20:23.309 --> 20:24.527
All of our names
will be on it.

20:24.571 --> 20:26.225
We'll make all the decisions
together.

20:26.268 --> 20:27.617
Well, Pope
won't give a shit,

20:27.661 --> 20:30.229
but Craig's gonna be pissed
he's back on allowance.

20:30.272 --> 20:32.361
Do you want me
to talk to him?

20:32.405 --> 20:34.885
[ Swallows ] No,
I'll talk to him.

20:37.888 --> 20:40.761
[ Footsteps approaching ]

20:40.804 --> 20:43.154
Excuse me, hon?

20:43.198 --> 20:44.939
Where's the,
uh, restroom?

20:44.982 --> 20:47.289
Uh, turn right,
and it's on your left.

20:47.333 --> 20:49.073
Great.

20:49.117 --> 20:57.778
♪♪

20:57.821 --> 20:59.910
[ Door opens ]

20:59.954 --> 21:07.918
♪♪

21:07.962 --> 21:15.970
♪♪

21:16.013 --> 21:17.319
[ Door opens ]

21:17.363 --> 21:19.756
[ Door closes ]

21:22.106 --> 21:23.499
[ Keypad beeps ]

21:23.543 --> 21:24.979
[ Door opens ]

21:26.067 --> 21:28.287
[ Door closes ]

21:28.330 --> 21:33.030
♪♪

21:33.074 --> 21:35.032
[ Keypad beeping ]

21:35.076 --> 21:42.953
♪♪

21:42.997 --> 21:45.304
[ Keypad beeps ]

21:45.347 --> 21:48.132
[ Keypad beeps ]

21:48.176 --> 21:50.483
Eddie: Mr. Smith.

21:52.136 --> 21:53.573
Eddie.

21:53.616 --> 21:56.271
Hey, I was just looking
for the bathroom.

21:56.315 --> 21:59.143
Uh, restroom's
right down there.

21:59.187 --> 22:01.972
You know,
I thought I missed it.

22:03.409 --> 22:05.498
Is that why you were
looking for cameras?

22:07.195 --> 22:09.328
[ Scoffs ] Excuse me?

22:09.371 --> 22:12.113
You can't see 'em,
but they're there.

22:12.156 --> 22:16.204
Just like the floor sensors
on those stairs.

22:16.247 --> 22:18.859
I just missed a turn.
That's all.

22:18.902 --> 22:22.253
Bro, I'm about to
drop 50 grand.

22:22.297 --> 22:25.039
Not anymore.

22:25.082 --> 22:30.523
♪♪

22:30.566 --> 22:31.654
Shit.

22:35.266 --> 22:39.401
Father Kirby: When Saul saw God,
he knew he was wrong

22:39.445 --> 22:41.969
for all the sins
that he had committed,

22:42.012 --> 22:46.060
and he didn't feel like
he was worthy of God's grace.

22:46.103 --> 22:48.105
Have any of you
ever felt that way?

22:48.149 --> 22:49.977
I certainly have.

22:50.020 --> 22:51.457
Yeah.

22:51.500 --> 22:53.763
Uh, sometimes
I yell at my mom.

22:53.807 --> 22:56.287
I-I feel bad later when she,
like,

22:56.331 --> 22:57.854
acts like
nothing happened.

22:57.898 --> 22:59.856
Yeah. Huh.

22:59.900 --> 23:02.511
How about you,
Andrew?

23:03.904 --> 23:06.080
Uh, yeah.

23:06.123 --> 23:08.430
Sometimes.

23:08.474 --> 23:09.866
I have bad thoughts.

23:09.910 --> 23:11.564
We all have bad thoughts,
Andrew.

23:11.607 --> 23:13.435
And sometimes,
we do bad things.

23:13.479 --> 23:14.828
But if you ask
for forgiveness,

23:14.871 --> 23:17.874
you will always receive
God's grace.

23:17.918 --> 23:21.051
You feel comfortable sharing
some of those thoughts?

23:21.095 --> 23:22.879
[ Knock on door ]

23:22.923 --> 23:24.054
It's open.

23:24.098 --> 23:25.404
[ Door opens ]

23:25.447 --> 23:27.493
Welcome.
-Thanks.

23:27.536 --> 23:30.409
I'm, uh --
I'm Andrew's brother, Barry.

23:30.452 --> 23:32.106
I'm just here to pick him up.
-Alright.

23:32.149 --> 23:33.977
Well, we're not
quite finished yet.

23:34.021 --> 23:37.241
Oh, well, uh,
I don't mind waiting.

23:38.329 --> 23:40.593
Okay, well, why don't you
grab a seat and join us?

23:40.636 --> 23:43.204
We got pizza on the way.
-Alright.

23:43.247 --> 23:47.426
♪♪

23:47.469 --> 23:48.905
Hey.

23:48.949 --> 23:51.430
Introduce me
to your friends.

23:51.473 --> 23:53.170
Franklin.

23:53.214 --> 23:54.650
Really like your jacket.

23:54.694 --> 23:57.566
Oh, thanks, man.
Franklin, huh?

23:57.610 --> 23:59.786
Like a hundred-dollar bill.

23:59.829 --> 24:02.223
He must be the one
buying the pizzas.

24:02.266 --> 24:03.572
[ Laughter ]

24:03.616 --> 24:05.487
-Excuse me, Barry.
-Sorry, Father.

24:05.531 --> 24:07.489
Father Kirby: Well,
let's open up our Bibles.

24:07.533 --> 24:10.231
So, when Saul
understood God's love,

24:10.274 --> 24:13.190
scales fell from his eyes.

24:13.234 --> 24:14.757
[ Sizzling ]

24:14.801 --> 24:16.672
So?

24:16.716 --> 24:19.458
Production's on-site,
but there's no chance
we're getting in there.

24:19.501 --> 24:21.503
What's the setup?

24:21.547 --> 24:23.766
Total lockdown.

24:23.810 --> 24:27.161
Cameras, floor sensors,
bio-locks, everything.

24:27.204 --> 24:30.033
So, we'll go in through the side
or the basement.

24:30.077 --> 24:32.514
It's a no-go. Walls
are poured concrete.

24:32.558 --> 24:33.907
Security isn't messing around,
either.

24:33.950 --> 24:35.256
It took them 30 seconds
to find me

24:35.299 --> 24:37.127
looking for the bathroom
in the wrong place.

24:37.171 --> 24:39.695
They gotta have a file cabinet
with every jewel in the world

24:39.739 --> 24:41.349
arranged by carat
or something.

24:41.392 --> 24:44.787
Look, man, all I know is that
they left 50 grand on the table.

24:44.831 --> 24:46.093
Alright, they took a picture
of my face,

24:46.136 --> 24:47.703
so I can't go back,
so that's it.

24:47.747 --> 24:49.488
What about the brother?
Did you see him?

24:49.531 --> 24:51.881
Yeah.
They treat him like dog crap.

24:51.925 --> 24:54.536
-That's our in.
-Yeah, I don't think so.

24:54.580 --> 24:55.798
Yeah, well,
you got a better idea?

24:55.842 --> 24:58.322
Yeah.
We find another job.

24:58.366 --> 25:00.542
I gotta go.
-Where?

25:00.586 --> 25:02.588
Craig: The gym.
I got shit to do.

25:02.631 --> 25:05.852
-We're not done here.
-Yeah? Well, I am.

25:07.767 --> 25:09.812
Whatever the hell's going on
between you two,

25:09.856 --> 25:12.772
you need to
work it out.

25:13.990 --> 25:16.166
Why are you so sure
the brother's the way in?

25:16.210 --> 25:18.125
Screwed him once,
he'll do it again.

25:18.168 --> 25:19.692
Yeah,
but it's his brother.

25:19.735 --> 25:21.824
His half-brother.

25:21.868 --> 25:23.130
So?

25:23.173 --> 25:25.915
Eddie's father remarried
and moved to California.

25:25.959 --> 25:27.830
He left Arthur
in Vietnam.

25:27.874 --> 25:30.180
Arthur only came over here
when he was an adult,

25:30.224 --> 25:33.009
so he's never really been
considered part of the family.

25:33.053 --> 25:37.144
Let me talk to him.
Alright?

25:39.059 --> 25:40.539
Talk to him.

25:40.582 --> 25:42.410
You didn't need
to pick me up.

25:42.453 --> 25:44.891
Hey, you needed
a ride home.

25:44.934 --> 25:47.894
Okay, fine.
Smurf's pissed you went back.

25:47.937 --> 25:49.983
Made me come get you.

25:50.026 --> 25:51.724
You could have
told her no.

25:51.767 --> 25:53.639
Come on, Andrew.

25:53.682 --> 25:55.858
What's the big deal
about this place anyway?

25:55.902 --> 25:58.426
They listen to me,
care what I think.

25:58.469 --> 26:01.560
Hey, I care.
Smurf cares.

26:01.603 --> 26:04.214
Okay, fine, she doesn't really
care what any of us think.

26:04.258 --> 26:06.477
-She cares what you think.
-Sometimes.

26:06.521 --> 26:08.088
-I don't want you here.
-Why?

26:08.131 --> 26:12.048
Everyone likes you.
I want this to be my thing.

26:12.092 --> 26:13.746
Cool.

26:13.789 --> 26:16.183
I don't really wanna be around
any of this church shit anyway.

26:16.226 --> 26:18.011
I was just trying to do
something to get Smurf

26:18.054 --> 26:19.926
off my ass.

26:21.884 --> 26:24.017
What did you do?

26:24.060 --> 26:26.454
I gave Julia one
of the computers.

26:26.497 --> 26:28.499
I was just doing something nice
for her, you know?

26:28.543 --> 26:30.632
She really misses school.

26:30.676 --> 26:32.373
[ Chuckles ]

26:32.416 --> 26:36.769
Hey, come on. Let's go home,
get some beers, take a swim.

26:38.597 --> 26:40.860
[ Engine starts ]

26:40.903 --> 26:42.949
[ Gear shifts ]

26:44.472 --> 26:46.082
[ Drill whirring ]

26:46.126 --> 26:48.607
-What's that about?
-What's up, man?

26:48.650 --> 26:50.913
Just let me skate!

26:50.957 --> 26:53.786
Oh. Punks already think
they own the place.

26:56.832 --> 26:59.269
-Aah!
-Goddamn it.

26:59.313 --> 27:02.446
Man: Do what?
You're real hard now, huh?

27:02.490 --> 27:05.275
Get up! Get up!

27:05.319 --> 27:06.929
-What the hell, man?!
-You get the hell out of here.

27:06.973 --> 27:08.931
What?! What did I do?
I didn't do anything.

27:08.975 --> 27:10.933
What's your problem?
-That was your fault.

27:10.977 --> 27:12.369
Bullshit. They were the ones
that started it.

27:12.413 --> 27:14.154
-They don't respect you.
-Oh, come on, man.

27:14.197 --> 27:15.895
What do you want me to do?
There's three of them.

27:15.938 --> 27:17.810
This is not a boxing match.
There's no referee.

27:17.853 --> 27:21.509
You pick up the board
and swing it, or you get out.

27:21.552 --> 27:24.207
Get out!

27:29.909 --> 27:32.781
-What? What do you want?
-Hey.

27:32.825 --> 27:34.783
-Oh!
-You want some?!

27:34.827 --> 27:37.656
-Yo.
-Bro, chill.

27:37.699 --> 27:40.180
We're good.

27:40.223 --> 27:48.971
♪♪

27:49.015 --> 27:50.364
[ Sighs ]

27:50.407 --> 27:53.149
It's got original tile
in both bathrooms, too.

27:53.193 --> 27:55.064
-Yeah, sounds sweet, man.
-[ Clears throat ]

27:55.108 --> 27:56.762
Yeah, you tell him about
the part where he has to

27:56.805 --> 27:59.503
take his shoes off
before he walks inside?

27:59.547 --> 28:01.723
Frank: Got 100-year-old
oak flooring throughout.

28:01.767 --> 28:03.638
I refinished them myself,
so...

28:03.682 --> 28:04.944
Hey, man, that sounds
good and all.

28:04.987 --> 28:08.034
I'm just not sure
I wanna move.

28:08.904 --> 28:11.690
He has a house on the beach.
Lot of eye candy.

28:11.733 --> 28:13.430
Lot of temptation.

28:13.474 --> 28:14.954
Mm.

28:14.997 --> 28:16.651
Feels hard to make
that change.

28:16.695 --> 28:18.000
Yeah. Okay.

28:18.044 --> 28:20.133
But she won't wait forever,
bro.

28:20.176 --> 28:21.395
Nope.

28:30.578 --> 28:32.754
[ Engine shuts off ]

28:37.977 --> 28:40.370
Not a good day
for ol' Chop.

28:40.414 --> 28:43.286
So, how'd you get that name,
anyway?

28:43.330 --> 28:45.724
Vince: Chop doesn't appreciate
people flipping him off.

28:45.767 --> 28:48.117
-Jesus Christ.
-What's up?

28:48.161 --> 28:53.732
I went to the gym,
and they said you were here.

28:53.775 --> 28:55.690
Who are you?

28:55.734 --> 28:57.387
I'm his brother.

28:57.431 --> 28:59.215
Yeah, that's Deran.

28:59.259 --> 29:01.740
What's up, man?

29:01.783 --> 29:04.133
I heard a lot about you.
I'm Vince.

29:05.831 --> 29:09.095
Can we talk?
Outside?

29:10.357 --> 29:12.838
Just deal me out.

29:16.102 --> 29:18.974
What the hell are you
even doing here, man?

29:21.934 --> 29:24.763
Said you were gonna be
at the gym.

29:24.806 --> 29:26.112
Are you kidding me?

29:26.155 --> 29:28.331
We're planning a job,
and you're playing cards

29:28.375 --> 29:31.682
with a bunch of random
biker dudes we don't even know.

29:31.726 --> 29:34.381
Random?

29:36.122 --> 29:38.037
Vince is my sponsor.
He's been looking out for me.

29:38.080 --> 29:39.473
-Oh, he's looking out for you?
-Yeah.

29:39.516 --> 29:40.822
Okay.

29:40.866 --> 29:42.302
[ Inhales sharply ]

29:42.345 --> 29:43.825
Could be a cop.

29:43.869 --> 29:45.653
But he's not a cop.

29:45.696 --> 29:46.959
How do you know that?

29:47.002 --> 29:49.178
Because I'm not sloppy
like you, Deran.

29:49.222 --> 29:52.094
The hell are you
even doing here, huh?

29:52.138 --> 29:54.096
I just wanted
to talk to you.

29:54.140 --> 29:55.924
-You wanna talk?
Alright. Well, talk.
-Yeah.

29:55.968 --> 29:57.970
You're not picking up
your phone.

29:58.013 --> 29:59.841
You're leaving
family meetings.

29:59.885 --> 30:02.757
You're [scoffs]
acting all different.

30:02.801 --> 30:05.804
I don't even recognize you
anymore, man.

30:05.847 --> 30:11.070
♪♪

30:11.113 --> 30:13.420
Everything okay?
We're about to start a new hand.

30:13.463 --> 30:15.465
Craig:
Yeah, man, we're fine.

30:15.509 --> 30:17.511
Hey, man, you're welcome
to play if you want.

30:17.554 --> 30:19.121
Nah.

30:19.165 --> 30:22.211
Deran was just leaving.

30:22.255 --> 30:27.826
♪♪

30:35.746 --> 30:36.965
[ Gear shifts ]

30:37.009 --> 30:39.576
[ Engine shuts off ]

30:48.542 --> 30:50.936
Hey, Arthur.

30:53.329 --> 30:56.245
I told you I never wanted
to see you again.

30:56.289 --> 30:57.856
I know.

30:57.899 --> 31:00.380
What do you want?

31:04.123 --> 31:06.690
I wanna
rip off your brother.

31:06.734 --> 31:09.171
And you want my help?

31:09.215 --> 31:10.956
Yes.

31:10.999 --> 31:13.697
[ Chuckles ]
Why would I do that?

31:13.741 --> 31:15.874
'Cause he treats you
like shit.

31:15.917 --> 31:17.701
You do all the work,

31:17.745 --> 31:20.182
and he ridicules you
in front of other people.

31:20.226 --> 31:22.532
A guy like that doesn't deserve
loyalty or respect,

31:22.576 --> 31:24.360
and you know that.

31:24.404 --> 31:27.015
That's why you let
the chopped stones go by.

31:28.103 --> 31:29.626
You wanted to hurt him.

31:29.670 --> 31:32.064
You don't know anything.
We're partners.

31:32.107 --> 31:33.543
It's a family business.

31:33.587 --> 31:35.415
Partners?

31:37.852 --> 31:39.549
Look at that house.

31:39.593 --> 31:41.900
You're leaving here,
while Eddie's living in

31:41.943 --> 31:44.728
that big house
in Laguna Beach,

31:44.772 --> 31:47.296
and you think
you're partners?

31:52.606 --> 31:56.610
Call me when you're ready to
start looking out for yourself.

32:08.143 --> 32:10.885
Why are we here, Smurf?

32:10.929 --> 32:16.847
Because it's time
that you all grew up

32:16.891 --> 32:21.287
and focused on
what really matters.

32:21.330 --> 32:23.419
This family.

32:26.031 --> 32:30.078
I've got a lead on a job,
and I want all of us to do it.

32:30.122 --> 32:32.733
Andrew's still
on probation.

32:32.776 --> 32:36.084
Doesn't matter, 'cause we're
not gonna get caught, right?

32:39.000 --> 32:42.047
There's 1,000 bucks in it
for each one of you.

32:44.179 --> 32:46.007
What is it?

32:46.051 --> 32:48.836
A house.

32:48.879 --> 32:50.664
Whose house?

32:50.707 --> 32:53.710
God's house.

32:57.062 --> 32:58.628
The rectory.

32:58.672 --> 33:00.891
-What?
-No.

33:00.935 --> 33:02.893
Baz already
scoped it out.

33:02.937 --> 33:07.333
It's got all of those silver
crosses and all the rest.

33:07.376 --> 33:11.424
It's -- It's a really good haul,
and we need the money.

33:11.467 --> 33:15.776
♪♪

33:15.819 --> 33:17.212
So?

33:17.256 --> 33:19.388
You know, you're the reason
that he's like this.

33:19.432 --> 33:22.130
There is nothing wrong
with your brother.

33:22.174 --> 33:24.306
Baz, come on.
I know you see it.

33:24.350 --> 33:27.657
Yeah, I mean, he's always
been like that, right?

33:27.701 --> 33:30.573
This is bullshit.

33:30.617 --> 33:35.317
♪♪

33:35.361 --> 33:38.277
Your brother
seemed upset.

33:38.320 --> 33:40.627
Everything okay?

33:40.670 --> 33:43.934
Yeah, man. It's just
some business shit.

33:43.978 --> 33:46.067
What kind of business?

33:46.111 --> 33:48.852
Look, don't worry, man,
alright?

33:48.896 --> 33:50.506
I can handle my brother.

33:50.550 --> 33:54.989
Still stressful. Family,
everything is personal,

33:55.033 --> 33:58.036
everything's a trigger,
alright?

33:58.079 --> 34:00.342
Yeah.

34:00.386 --> 34:02.823
Gotta make a living,
though, right?

34:02.866 --> 34:05.173
There's other ways
of making a living.

34:05.217 --> 34:08.437
All I'm saying is it don't
have to be with family.

34:08.481 --> 34:14.791
♪♪

34:14.835 --> 34:18.491
-Thanks for the game. Alright?
-Yeah. For sure.

34:20.580 --> 34:22.799
[ Door opens ]

34:22.843 --> 34:24.714
Hey.

34:24.758 --> 34:28.718
♪♪

34:29.719 --> 34:31.765
You okay?

34:34.246 --> 34:37.423
You know, we don't
have to do it.

34:38.641 --> 34:42.080
If we all told Smurf no,
she couldn't make us.

34:42.123 --> 34:49.522
♪♪

34:49.565 --> 34:56.616
♪♪

34:56.659 --> 34:59.314
Think the trust
is a good idea.

34:59.358 --> 35:02.187
I think
you should go for it.

35:02.230 --> 35:05.103
And things are gonna change,
like you said.

35:05.146 --> 35:07.322
You think
Craig's okay with it?

35:07.366 --> 35:10.108
He'll come around to it
eventually.

35:10.151 --> 35:12.458
He always does.

35:13.807 --> 35:15.678
[ Engine shuts off ]

35:20.944 --> 35:22.685
What are you doing later?

35:22.729 --> 35:24.905
You wanna get a drink
or something?

35:24.948 --> 35:26.646
I can't.
I got plans.

35:27.603 --> 35:30.128
This is my uncle
Deran.

35:30.171 --> 35:32.130
You have another one?

35:37.265 --> 35:39.311
[ Lighter clicks ]

35:44.490 --> 35:46.666
So?
What you got for us?

35:46.709 --> 35:50.322
There's no way I can get you
into the store.

35:50.365 --> 35:52.193
Security checks me, too.

35:52.237 --> 35:54.978
And my brother pays them
to be there 24/7.

35:55.022 --> 35:56.893
What about deliveries?

35:56.937 --> 36:00.245
Armed courier.
Same ones every time.

36:00.288 --> 36:02.464
Only people Eddie trusts.

36:02.508 --> 36:04.640
And if you show up instead
of his regular courier,

36:04.684 --> 36:07.687
security would drop you
on the spot.

36:09.254 --> 36:10.951
Well, shit.

36:13.519 --> 36:15.564
If you're gonna do this,

36:15.608 --> 36:17.827
you're gonna have to do it
off-site.

36:17.871 --> 36:19.916
Do you know
who Brock Fellows is?

36:19.960 --> 36:21.483
-The singer?
-Yeah.

36:21.527 --> 36:24.138
Super Bowl halftime show
and all that?
-Yeah.

36:24.182 --> 36:26.749
He's throwing a birthday party
for his girlfriend in two weeks,

36:26.793 --> 36:29.099
and he's renting a few
of Eddie's favorite pieces

36:29.143 --> 36:31.319
as "decoration."

36:31.363 --> 36:34.627
How much total
in pieces?

36:34.670 --> 36:38.457
If you got all of it,
at least 750K.

36:38.500 --> 36:40.676
You could get us
into this party?

36:40.720 --> 36:43.679
No. All I can tell you
is when and where.

36:43.723 --> 36:46.900
-And what's your end?
-50%.

36:48.771 --> 36:50.773
20%.

36:50.817 --> 36:52.514
30%.

36:52.558 --> 36:54.864
It's time to take care
of myself, right?

36:54.908 --> 36:59.869
♪♪

36:59.913 --> 37:02.872
25%, and we'll guarantee you
50 grand.

37:02.916 --> 37:05.223
♪♪

37:05.266 --> 37:08.051
Keep the phone.
We'll be in touch.

37:08.095 --> 37:11.664
♪♪

37:16.756 --> 37:18.279
Penny:
I got off pretty easy.

37:18.323 --> 37:20.238
I mean,
only six months probation.

37:20.281 --> 37:22.152
-How old were you?
-Uh, 15.

37:22.196 --> 37:24.154
I just had to have
that lipstick.

37:24.198 --> 37:25.721
And I almost got away
with it, too.

37:25.765 --> 37:27.897
I was halfway out the door when
the security guard grabbed me.

37:27.941 --> 37:30.160
Did he take you
into the back room?

37:30.204 --> 37:31.727
Oh, yeah.
You been in it?

37:31.771 --> 37:33.555
No. I just --
I just heard about it.

37:33.599 --> 37:34.861
Well, anyway,
I threw up,

37:34.904 --> 37:37.820
and then I told them
everything immediately.

37:37.864 --> 37:41.302
What about you?
Any peak high school moments?

37:41.346 --> 37:43.739
No.
I mostly studied.

37:43.783 --> 37:45.654
What a nerd.

37:45.698 --> 37:48.875
Oh. Shit. I'm gonna have to
get this dry-cleaned.

37:51.181 --> 37:53.358
Dressing up
was your idea.

37:53.401 --> 37:54.837
I thought we were going
somewhere nice.

37:54.881 --> 37:57.710
This isnice.
I mean, look at that view.

37:57.753 --> 37:59.886
Sure.
Sure, it's great.

37:59.929 --> 38:01.670
I didn't -- I didn't need to
wear a suit, though.

38:01.714 --> 38:04.325
Yeah, you did.
I wanted to see you in one.

38:04.369 --> 38:06.675
I knew you'd look good.

38:06.719 --> 38:08.982
[ Chuckles ]

38:09.025 --> 38:11.854
Aren't you gonna tell me
I look good, too?

38:19.340 --> 38:27.305
♪♪

38:27.348 --> 38:35.313
♪♪

38:36.401 --> 38:40.709
I told you, they have thebest
calamari outside of Spain.

38:40.753 --> 38:42.972
Are you ready for dessert?

38:43.016 --> 38:44.887
Uh...

38:44.931 --> 38:46.759
I think
we still need a minute.

38:46.802 --> 38:49.414
I'll take another one
of these, please.

38:49.457 --> 38:50.980
Thanks.

38:51.024 --> 38:52.286
[ Whispers ]
Bad boy.

38:52.330 --> 38:54.810
♪♪

38:54.854 --> 38:56.334
So?

38:56.377 --> 39:00.555
♪♪

39:00.599 --> 39:02.035
We're almost done
with dinner.

39:02.078 --> 39:05.908
You have said five words
the entire time.

39:07.954 --> 39:11.044
I thought we were gonna
get to know each other.

39:12.915 --> 39:15.178
Okay.
What do you want to know?

39:15.222 --> 39:17.355
Alright.

39:18.965 --> 39:21.750
Have you ever been in
a serious relationship before?

39:21.794 --> 39:23.535
Yeah.

39:23.578 --> 39:26.233
Alright.
For how long?

39:26.276 --> 39:28.322
Thank you.

39:28.366 --> 39:30.498
♪♪

39:30.542 --> 39:32.457
♪ There's too much smoke
to see it ♪

39:32.500 --> 39:34.850
A long time.

39:34.894 --> 39:38.114
♪ There's too much broke
to feel this ♪

39:38.158 --> 39:40.900
♪ Well, I love you,
I love you ♪

39:40.943 --> 39:43.468
So, what happened?

39:43.511 --> 39:44.991
My mom wanted
to kill him.

39:45.034 --> 39:46.122
[ Laughs ]

39:46.166 --> 39:48.864
♪ There's too much smoke
to see it ♪

39:48.908 --> 39:51.519
I would say your mom
sounds like a trip.

39:51.563 --> 39:52.868
So, where is she now?

39:52.912 --> 39:56.350
♪ I love you,
I love you ♪

39:56.394 --> 39:59.309
♪ And all of your pieces

39:59.353 --> 40:01.355
[ Sets glass down ]

40:01.399 --> 40:04.140
I gotta piss.

40:04.184 --> 40:13.802
♪♪

40:13.846 --> 40:21.157
♪♪

40:21.201 --> 40:28.469
♪♪

40:28.513 --> 40:30.906
What a world, right?

40:32.473 --> 40:34.649
-Hmm?
-Look at that.

40:34.693 --> 40:36.521
Used to be these fairies
had their own places to go,

40:36.564 --> 40:38.261
but now,
it's right in our faces.

40:38.305 --> 40:39.741
It wasn't like that
when I was growing up.

40:39.785 --> 40:42.570
Back then,
someone would do something.

40:42.614 --> 40:45.747
Like what?

40:45.791 --> 40:49.490
You know,
straighten them out.

40:49.534 --> 40:51.753
♪ There's too much smoke
to see it ♪

40:51.797 --> 40:54.234
♪ There's too much broke
to feel this ♪

40:54.277 --> 40:56.105
Okay.

40:56.149 --> 41:00.588
I'll get one of them to come
in the back alley with me.

41:00.632 --> 41:03.417
You can follow behind.

41:03.461 --> 41:05.941
We can have some fun.

41:05.985 --> 41:07.421
♪ There's too much broke
to feel this ♪

41:07.465 --> 41:09.118
[ Laughs ]

41:09.162 --> 41:11.556
♪ I love you,
I love you ♪

41:11.599 --> 41:13.775
Just don't pussy out
like a little bitch.

41:13.819 --> 41:16.256
♪ And all of your pieces

41:16.299 --> 41:19.738
♪ History's a letter
made of scarlet ♪

41:19.781 --> 41:22.218
Can you come outside with me
for a second?

41:24.177 --> 41:26.701
I need you.

41:26.745 --> 41:30.575
We'll talk later.

41:30.618 --> 41:40.280
♪♪

41:40.323 --> 41:49.942
♪♪

41:49.985 --> 41:59.429
♪♪

41:59.473 --> 42:06.001
♪♪

42:06.045 --> 42:08.221
-Go stand over there.
-What?

42:08.264 --> 42:09.875
I don't want to do it here.
Go stand over there.

42:09.918 --> 42:12.486
-Why?
-Just do it.

42:12.530 --> 42:21.321
♪♪

42:21.364 --> 42:23.845
Let's do this.

42:23.889 --> 42:26.892
What are you doing?
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

42:26.935 --> 42:28.546
Deran.

42:28.589 --> 42:31.592
♪♪

42:31.636 --> 42:33.986
Stop!

42:34.029 --> 42:36.205
Oh, my God.

42:36.249 --> 42:37.903
Deran.

42:40.558 --> 42:43.212
Oh, God!

42:43.256 --> 42:44.779
Deran.

42:45.998 --> 42:47.652
Deran, what are you doing?!

42:47.695 --> 42:49.523
Stop!
-You want a piece of me?

42:49.567 --> 42:50.698
Is that what you wanted?

42:50.742 --> 42:53.701
Deran.
You gotta stop.

42:53.745 --> 42:59.185
♪♪

42:59.228 --> 43:02.362
[ Coughing ]

43:02.405 --> 43:04.669
[ Laughing ]

43:04.712 --> 43:10.239
♪♪

43:10.283 --> 43:12.720
[ Sighs ]

43:12.764 --> 43:15.897
♪♪

43:15.941 --> 43:18.639
That guy's
a piece of shit.

43:18.683 --> 43:20.119
[ Scoffs ]

43:21.511 --> 43:23.601
[ Spits ]

43:55.328 --> 43:56.459
You're here early.

43:56.503 --> 43:58.461
Just been couch surfing.

43:58.505 --> 44:01.116
My friend kicked me out
to be with this chick.

44:01.160 --> 44:03.641
You're really good,
you know?

44:03.684 --> 44:05.686
I don't know about that.

44:07.557 --> 44:11.083
Look, I just wanted to say thank
you for the advice yesterday.

44:11.126 --> 44:14.652
You know, if you ever need any
help, you can just let me know.

44:14.695 --> 44:17.480
You don't have to
work to come here.

44:17.524 --> 44:20.658
I don't have anything
today.

44:20.701 --> 44:22.703
But maybe tomorrow.

44:22.747 --> 44:25.488
But if you work,
you get paid, got it?

44:25.532 --> 44:27.534
Okay.

44:27.577 --> 44:30.015
Tomorrow, then.

44:45.726 --> 44:50.775
♪♪

44:50.818 --> 44:52.167
[ Car door closes ]

44:52.211 --> 44:58.043
♪♪

44:58.086 --> 45:01.089
How much longer I gotta do this?
-As long as I need you to.

45:01.133 --> 45:04.310
-This is bullshit.
-No, it's not.

45:04.353 --> 45:08.009
♪♪

45:08.053 --> 45:12.187
Go back tomorrow.
Keep me posted, okay?

45:13.406 --> 45:16.061
Put some ice
on that eye.

45:18.585 --> 45:20.413
Alright.

45:20.456 --> 45:30.423
♪♪

